Evaluating the two candidates against those stated preferences:
- Tapestry: tactile, mic‑forward grand piano; single front‑and‑center conversational female vocal; sparse arrangements and restrained color; analogue, low‑compression mastering that preserves dynamics and midrange clarity; concise 3–4 minute songs and intimate, cohesive sequencing. These characteristics directly match my prized attributes — tactile piano timbre, close‑up vocal presentation with preserved microdynamics, low‑compression/analogue mastering, natural midrange focus, and carefully sequenced, concise tracks for attentive listening.
