Because my strongest, repeated preferences emphasize tactile piano-led intimacy, preserved midrange microdynamics, low‑compression analogue mastering, and concise, cohesive sequencing—qualities explicitly present in Tapestry—Tapestry aligns more directly with my core listening values. While the vocal‑forward synth‑pop remaster shares many technical strengths and would be an attractive second choice (especially for its analogue warmth and preserved transients), it carries greater risk of produced, rhythm‑forward presentation and a less purely intimate, piano‑and‑voice midrange focus than Tapestry. For those reasons I choose Tapestry and reject the synth‑pop remaster.

