How the two candidates map to those criteria
- Groove‑ and bass‑forward funk compilation: described as punchy, prominent low end, louder/denser mastering with heavier limiting, rhythm‑first lock‑step bass/drums that reduce transient snap, and buried close vocal intimacy. That directly conflicts with my core needs: heavy limiting and loudness‑driven mastering destroy preserved transients and microdynamics; a dominant low end and rhythm‑first approach run counter to the “tactile upright bass only when appropriate” and to mixes that let instruments and the lead breathe. The description explicitly says it diminishes tape‑like micro‑dynamics and buries close vocal intimacy — both major red flags for me.
